# Git commits and pull requests

## Do not name tools or assistants

Never mention **Cursor**, **Copilot**, other IDE or coding-assistant products, or meta phrases like “AI-generated”, “chat said”, or “prompt output” in:

- Commit messages (subject or body)
- PR titles or descriptions
- Merge commit messages
- Review replies that get copied into permanent history

Write like internal engineering notes: **what changed**, **why**, and **how to verify**. Use conventional, neutral tone (e.g. imperative subject: `Add budget rollover validation`).

## Comments in code

Do not add comments that reference Cursor, assistants, or “generated” provenance. Explain **intent** or **non-obvious behaviour** only when it helps maintainers.
